title: Trojans spoil Viking Classic hosts' title dreams
text:
Trojans spoil Viking Classic hosts' title dreams 
Winnipeg’s Vincent Massey Trojans swept the varsity girls’ and boys’ titles at the Viking Classic volleyball tournament on the weekend and left the host Vincent Massey sides disappointed. 
The Trojans ended the title dreams of both Viking squads, beating the girls in the final and the boys in the semifinals. 
Although Vikings varsity girls’ head coach Mike DeGroot would have liked to see his team win its home tournament, he was proud of his players. Massey, which is fifth in the provincial AAAA rankings, was in the toughest pool at the tournament with the second-ranked Trojans, ninth-ranked Glenlawn Lions and 10th-ranked Northlands Parkway Nighthawks. They beat the Lions, split with the Nighthawks and lost to the Trojans.
